.TH "SPEECHRECOGNITION.CONTINUOUS" "3JS" "September 30, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SpeechRecognition.continuous \- SpeechRecognition: continuous property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]continuous\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]SpeechRecognition\f[R] interface controls whether continuous
results are returned for each recognition, or only a single result.
.PP
It defaults to single results (\f[CR]false\f[R].)
.SH VALUE
A boolean value representing the current
\f[CR]SpeechRecognition\f[R]\(cqs continuous status.
\f[CR]true\f[R] means continuous, and \f[CR]false\f[R] means not
continuous (single result each time.)
.SH EXAMPLES
This code is excerpted from our \c
.UR https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/blob/main/web-speech-api/speech-color-changer/script.js
Speech color changer
.UE \c
\ example.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] recognition = \f[B]new\f[R] SpeechRecognition();
recognition.continuous = \f[B]false\f[R];
recognition.lang = \(dqen\-US\(dq;
recognition.interimResults = \f[B]false\f[R];
recognition.maxAlternatives = 1;

\f[I]// \&...\f[R]
.EE
